Nonsense. Expensive is not the requirement. Turning a money-cannon on problems and spending as much of the taxpayer's money on things as possible to satisfy political graft isn't the requirement either. Look at the Shutle experience to see what overly expensive too-complex stuff does for you. You don't always get what you pay for.<br>
<br>
The manufacturers have a selection of the latest tested equipment. From suits to HLVs.<br>
 The way of making the stuff cheaper to make and acquire in this case favors the better quality: There's no good reason why a Titan rocket costs more than a 747, so which one would you rather count on for a lifetime of service? (or a few seasons anyway) The only reason  for the difference is the way it's treated by management.<br>
 Don't just slap something together, but don't treat everything as an inherently massively expensive government program either. &quot;An elephant is a mouse built to government specifications&quot; just about sums it up.<br>
<br>
I'm sorry, I'll listen to Freeman Dyson, Ray Bradbury, Pournelle, Walker and others who don't have a political stake in spending lots of money but have the heart to accept minimal risks and the sense to build something to do a purpose, instead of to spend lots of money, before I'll listen to a government bureaucrat in this (likening the money cannon approach to their operating paradigm). <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=johnfraz>John Fraz</A> at: 1/17/04 6:54 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=babbler36>Babbler36</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Lurker</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/18/04 1:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=993.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/7.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: What It Is About</span><hr size=1> The problem is money with private space programs. It take <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.jetpress.org/volume4/space.htm" target="top">large sums of money to finiance</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, which can only be brought on by government agencies.<br>
